# vDSP_deq22D

**Function**

Performs two-pole two-zero recursive filtering on a double-precision vector.

## Declaration

```swift
extern void vDSP_deq22D(const double * __A, vDSP_Stride __IA, const double * __B, double * __C, vDSP_Stride __IC, vDSP_Length __N);
```

## Discussion

This function is the same as [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/kernel/1532225-vdsp_deq22], except for the types of vectors `A`, `B`, and `C`..

## Vector-to-Vector Recursive Filtering on Real Vectors

- **vDSP_deq22**: Performs two-pole two-zero recursive filtering on a single-precision vector.
